cme@ellisun.sw.stratus.com (Carl Ellison) writes:
: 
: As far as I know, (1) there is no unique identifier in PCs; (3) dates are
: provided by a human user rather than by radio from some time standard; and
: (2) most people asking this question want to be able to mass produce
: software (eg, on CD-ROM) so that all copies are identical.
The only way round this is if the PC has an ethernet card fitted, that will
take care of the unique identifier.
Other than that there appears no-way round this, any user of a PC an quite
easily alter things like the date.
